   <text>
      <body>
         <opener>
            <dateline><date when="1868-01-26">January 26, 1868.</date></dateline>
            <salute>Miss Dodge.</salute>
            <salute>otherwise,<lb/>
            My dear Gail Hamilton</salute>
         </opener>
         
         <p>A book is in prospect. The title is to be, Eminent Women of our time. You and I, are to figure in it. <hi rend="underline">I</hi> am to do <hi rend="underline">you</hi>! 
            Who is to take me the gods know. Meantime I desire to know at what age you cut your first tooth, and where. Also whether you had the measles before the mumps, 
            or the mumps before the measles. Also, any other interesting items about yourself, which you can furnish me at your earliest convenience. It will be a labor 
            of love with me, because I rejoice every day in your existence. In short you are one of the women I believe in. So dont be stingy of facts. Horace Greeley, 
         Theodore Tilton, my husband, &amp; others are all to "do" somebody. It is intended, that the book shall be handsomely got up, in every respect. There you 
         are&#8212;please send me an early response.</p>
         
         <closer>
            <salute>Yours very truly</salute>
            <signed>Fanny Fern Parton</signed>
            <address>
               <addrLine>303. East Eighteenth St. New York</addrLine>
            </address>
         </closer>
      </body>
